BBMan License Notice
====================

The imported upstream source declares the project license as:

    GPL : http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html

The original imported `license` file is kept unchanged. No exact GPL version
number was written in the imported CVS tree.

BBMan was originally released in the GPLv2 era, before GPLv3 existed. This
maintained fork is therefore conservatively conveyed under GNU GPL version 2.
The full GPLv2 text is provided in `LICENSE`.

Basis for selecting GPLv2
-------------------------

* The imported upstream files and the original `license` file identify the
  license as GPL and point to the GNU GPL URL.
* The upstream source dates from 2004, when that GNU GPL URL referred to
  GPLv2; GPLv3 did not exist until 2007.
* The imported upstream source does not specify a GPL version number.
* GPLv2 section 9 says that, when a program does not specify a GPL version
  number, recipients may choose any version published by the Free Software
  Foundation.
* As the maintainer and distributor of this maintained fork, Keng-Yu Lin
  selects GPLv2 as the version used to convey the fork. This makes the
  selected GPL version explicit without claiming that the original upstream
  author wrote a more specific license notice.

This notice does not relicense the original upstream code. It records the GPL
version selected for conveying this maintained fork. Porting changes by
Keng-Yu Lin are distributed under the same GPLv2 terms.

The historical embedded libssh copy under `legacy/ssh-libssh/` has its own
LGPL notice and copying text in that subtree. The active wx3 build does not
compile or link that embedded libssh code.
